article.headline: Youngstown St. 82, Detroit 70
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Quin Humphrey scored 36 points and Youngstown State rallied in the final minutes to beat Detroit 82-70 on Wednesday night. Humphrey was 12-of-18 shooting, hitting eight 3-pointers on 12 attempts. Keston Roberts added 19 points and Jack Liles had 12 rebounds for Youngstown State (11-15, 6-8 Horizon League), which trailed 42-36 at the half. Detroit (9-17, 5-9) led by as much as 10 points in the second period, but the Penguins scored nine straight points to take a 68-66 lead on a 3-pointer and foul shot from Humphrey with 4:46 remaining. The Penguins widened their lead to eight before Jon Goode scored Detroit's last basket on a layup with 1:05 left to make it 76-70. Youngstown State hit two foul shots and two layups to seal the game. Ryvon Covile and Zach Everingham each had 16 points and Goode added 10 for Detroit. Nemanja Jokic had seven rebounds. The Penguins shot 50 percent (30-of-60), while the Titans shot 47 percent (29-of-62). Youngstown State outrebounded Detroit 40-30.
